Hong Kong’s Tsang May Unveil Subsidized Housing Plan, Economic Times Says

-- B y   M a r k   L e e
-- 
2011-06-18T06:11:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-18/hong-kong-s-tsang-may-unveil-subsidized-housing-plan-economic-times-says.html
The Hong Kong government may unveil
a plan to resume the construction of subsidized housing after
property prices in the city surged, the  Hong Kong Economic Times 
reported, citing people it didn’t identify. Chief Executive
Donald Tsang may disclose details of the plan to resume the
program known as Home Ownership Scheme in his policy address to
the legislature, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mark Lee in Hong Kong at 
 wlee37@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Malcolm Scott at 
 mscott23@bloomberg.net  